{"word":"ἀνθηρός","slug":"ἀνθηρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνθηρός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀνθέω'><el>ἀνθέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>flowering, blooming</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>blooming, fresh</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἀνθηρὸν μένος</el> rage <i>bursting into flower</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>at its height</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>bright-coloured, bright</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>τὸ ἀνθ.</el> <i>brightness</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}